  "doc_id": "38826",
  "text": "Many non-CC metaheuristic algorithms are recognized as effective approaches for solving large scale optimization problems. Actually, as documented in the summary reports of the competitions on large-scale global optimization at CEC'2010, CEC'2012, CEC'2013, and CEC'2015, the winner has been a non-CC metaheuristic algorithm. For this reason, we also compare MMO-CC with six metaheuristic non-CC algorithms: 2S-Ensemble [CITATION_1] , GaDE [CITATION_2] , jDElscop [CITATION_3] , MA-SWChains [CITATION_4] , MOS-CEC2012 [CITATION_5] , and MOS-CEC2013 [CITATION_6] . The descriptions of these compared algorithms are summarized in Table S -IV in the supplementary material. Note that DECC-G is used for comparison as a baseline algorithm.",
